          {
            "title": "Lesson #4",
            "id": 132720,
            "contentType": "interactive",
            "images": [],
            "interactiveContent": "<!DOCTYPE html ><html><body><p>Ao usar queries parametrizadas, também podemos usar múltiplos placeholders. No entanto, devemos manter a ordem em mente!</p><code version=\"2\" codelang=\"javascript\" name=\"script.js\" visible-if=\"always\"><content><text value=\"const\" class=\"keyword\" /><text value=\" Database = \" /><text value=\"require\" class=\"built_in\" /><text value=\"(\" /><text value=\"&quot;better-sqlite3&quot;\" class=\"string\" /><text value=\");\" /><text type=\"break\" /><text value=\"const\" class=\"keyword\" /><text value=\" db = \" /><text value=\"new\" class=\"keyword\" /><text value=\" Database(\" /><text value=\"&quot;database.db&quot;\" class=\"string\" /><text value=\");\" /><text type=\"break\" /><text type=\"break\" /><text value=\"const\" class=\"keyword\" /><text value=\" query = db.prepare(\" /><text value=\"&quot;SELECT * FROM users WHERE name = ? AND age = ?&quot;\" class=\"string\" /><text value=\");\" /><text type=\"break\" /><text value=\"const\" class=\"keyword\" /><text value=\" user = query.get(\" /><text value=\"&quot;Bob&quot;\" class=\"string\" /><text value=\", \" /><text value=\"25\" class=\"number\" /><text value=\");\" /><text type=\"break\" /><text type=\"break\" /><text value=\"console\" class=\"built_in\" /><text value=\".log(user);\" /></content><interactions><interaction type=\"fillTheGap\" isDefault=\"true\"><options><option startIndex=\"191\" endIndex=\"193\" /><option startIndex=\"184\" endIndex=\"189\" /><option startIndex=\"144\" endIndex=\"145\" /><option startIndex=\"156\" endIndex=\"157\" /></options></interaction></interactions><output><content><text value=\"{ id: 890, name: &quot;Bob&quot; }\" /></content></output></code><p visible-if=\"wrong\">Certifique-se de escolher <code>?</code> seguido de <code>?</code> e depois <code>\"Bob\"</code>, <code>25</code>.</p></body></html>"
          },
          {
            "title": "Lesson #5",
            "id": 132721,
            "contentType": "interactive",
            "images": [],
            "interactiveContent": "<!DOCTYPE html ><html><body><p>Vamos tentar usar três parâmetros na declaração.</p><code version=\"2\" codelang=\"javascript\" name=\"script.js\" visible-if=\"always\"><content><text value=\"const\" class=\"keyword\" /><text value=\" Database = \" /><text value=\"require\" class=\"built_in\" /><text value=\"(\" /><text value=\"&quot;better-sqlite3&quot;\" class=\"string\" /><text value=\");\" /><text type=\"break\" /><text value=\"const\" class=\"keyword\" /><text value=\" db = \" /><text value=\"new\" class=\"keyword\" /><text value=\" Database(\" /><text value=\"&quot;database.db&quot;\" class=\"string\" /><text value=\");\" /><text type=\"break\" /><text type=\"break\" /><text value=\"const\" class=\"keyword\" /><text value=\" query = db.prepare(\" /><text value=\"&quot;SELECT * FROM products WHERE name = ? AND price = ? AND category = ?&quot;\" class=\"string\" /><text value=\");\" /><text type=\"break\" /><text value=\"const\" class=\"keyword\" /><text value=\" product = query.get(\" /><text value=\"&quot;Laptop&quot;\" class=\"string\" /><text value=\", \" /><text value=\"999.99\" class=\"number\" /><text value=\", \" /><text value=\"&quot;Electronics&quot;\" class=\"string\" /><text value=\");\" /><text type=\"break\" /><text type=\"break\" /><text value=\"console\" class=\"built_in\" /><text value=\".log(product);\" /><text type=\"break\" /></content><interactions><interaction type=\"fillTheGap\" isDefault=\"true\"><options><option startIndex=\"209\" endIndex=\"217\" /><option startIndex=\"219\" endIndex=\"222\" /><option startIndex=\"222\" endIndex=\"223\" /><option startIndex=\"223\" endIndex=\"225\" /><option startIndex=\"227\" endIndex=\"240\" /><option startIndex=\"147\" endIndex=\"148\" /><option startIndex=\"161\" endIndex=\"162\" /><option startIndex=\"178\" endIndex=\"179\" /></options></interaction></interactions><output><content><text value=\"{ id: 19, name: '&quot;Laptop&quot;, price: 999.99, category: &quot;Electronics&quot; }\" /></content></output></code><p visible-if=\"wrong\">Certifique-se de escolher <code>?</code> seguido de <code>?</code> e depois <code>?</code>, <code>\"Laptop\"</code>, <code>999</code>, <code>.</code>, <code>99</code>, <code>\"Electronics\"</code>.</p></body></html>"
          },
          {
            "title": "Lesson #6",
            "id": 132722,
            "contentType": "interactive",
            "images": [],
            "interactiveContent": "<!DOCTYPE html ><html><body><p>Também podemos passar os parâmetros em um array para a função <code>get</code>, mas ainda precisamos manter a ordem em mente.</p><code version=\"2\" codelang=\"javascript\" name=\"script.js\" visible-if=\"always\"><content><text value=\"const\" class=\"keyword\" /><text value=\" Database = \" /><text value=\"require\" class=\"built_in\" /><text value=\"(\" /><text value=\"&quot;better-sqlite3&quot;\" class=\"string\" /><text value=\");\" /><text type=\"break\" /><text value=\"const\" class=\"keyword\" /><text value=\" db = \" /><text value=\"new\" class=\"keyword\" /><text value=\" Database(\" /><text value=\"&quot;library.db&quot;\" class=\"string\" /><text value=\");\" /><text type=\"break\" /><text type=\"break\" /><text value=\"const\" class=\"keyword\" /><text value=\" query = db.prepare(\" /><text value=\"&quot;SELECT * FROM books WHERE title = ? AND author = ?&quot;\" class=\"string\" /><text value=\");\" /><text type=\"break\" /><text value=\"const\" class=\"keyword\" /><text value=\" book = query.get([\" /><text value=\"&quot;1984&quot;\" class=\"string\" /><text value=\", \" /><text value=\"&quot;George Orwell&quot;\" class=\"string\" /><text value=\"]);\" /><text type=\"break\" /><text type=\"break\" /><text value=\"console\" class=\"built_in\" /><text value=\".log(book);\" /><text type=\"break\" /></content><interactions><interaction type=\"fillTheGap\" isDefault=\"true\"><options><option startIndex=\"144\" endIndex=\"145\" /><option startIndex=\"159\" endIndex=\"160\" /><option startIndex=\"188\" endIndex=\"195\" /><option startIndex=\"196\" endIndex=\"211\" /></options></interaction></interactions><output><content><text value=\"{ id: 1, title: &quot;1984&quot;, author: &quot;George Orwell&quot;, year: 1949 }\" /></content></output></code><p visible-if=\"wrong\">Certifique-se de escolher <code>?</code> seguido de <code>?</code> e depois <code>\"1984\",</code>, <code>\"George Orwell\"</code>.</p></body></html>"
          },
          {
            "title": "Lesson #4",
            "id": 132705,
            "contentType": "interactive",
            "images": [],
            "interactiveContent": "<!DOCTYPE html ><html><body><p>Ao criar endpoints, frequentemente usamos os parâmetros de rota ou de consulta para identificar o elemento que queremos obter, atualizar ou deletar.</p><p>Neste caso, usamos o parâmetro de rota <code>id</code> para criar uma consulta com base nas necessidades do nosso cliente.</p><code version=\"2\" codelang=\"javascript\" name=\"app.js\" visible-if=\"always\"><content><text value=\"app.get(\" /><text value=\"&quot;/product/:id&quot;\" class=\"string\" /><text value=\", (req, res) =&gt; {\" /><text type=\"break\" /><text value=\"  \" /><text value=\"const\" class=\"keyword\" /><text value=\" query = db.prepare(\" /><text value=\"&quot;SELECT * FROM products WHERE id = ?&quot;\" class=\"string\" /><text value=\");\" /><text type=\"break\" /><text value=\"  \" /><text value=\"const\" class=\"keyword\" /><text value=\" product = query.get(req.params.id);\" /><text type=\"break\" /><text value=\"  \" /><text type=\"break\" /><text value=\"  res.send(product);\" /><text type=\"break\" /><text value=\"});\" /></content><interactions><interaction type=\"fillTheGap\" isDefault=\"true\"><options><option startIndex=\"97\" endIndex=\"103\" /><option startIndex=\"135\" endIndex=\"148\" /><option startIndex=\"19\" endIndex=\"21\" /></options></interaction></interactions></code><p visible-if=\"wrong\">Certifique-se de escolher <code>id</code> seguido de <code>id = ?</code> e finalmente <code>req.params.id</code>.</p></body></html>"
          },
          {
            "title": "Lesson #6",
            "id": 132707,
            "contentType": "interactive",
            "images": [],
            "interactiveContent": "<!DOCTYPE html ><html><body><p>Às vezes, podemos querer usar mais de um <code>?</code> em uma declaração. Vamos ver um exemplo onde recebemos três valores do cliente.</p><code version=\"2\" codelang=\"javascript\" name=\"app.js\" visible-if=\"always\"><content><text value=\"app.put(\" /><text value=\"&quot;/user/:id&quot;\" class=\"string\" /><text value=\", (req, res) =&gt; {\" /><text type=\"break\" /><text value=\"  \" /><text value=\"const\" class=\"keyword\" /><text value=\" query = db.prepare(\" /><text value=\"&quot;UPDATE users SET name = ?, age = ? WHERE id = ?&quot;\" class=\"string\" /><text value=\");\" /><text type=\"break\" /><text value=\"  query.run(req.body.name, req.body.age, req.params.id);\" /><text type=\"break\" /><text value=\"  res.send(\" /><text value=\"&quot;User Updated!&quot;\" class=\"string\" /><text value=\");\" /><text type=\"break\" /><text value=\"});\" /></content><interactions><interaction type=\"fillTheGap\" isDefault=\"true\"><options><option startIndex=\"128\" endIndex=\"141\" /><option startIndex=\"143\" endIndex=\"155\" /><option startIndex=\"157\" endIndex=\"170\" /><option startIndex=\"89\" endIndex=\"90\" /><option startIndex=\"98\" endIndex=\"99\" /><option startIndex=\"111\" endIndex=\"112\" /></options></interaction></interactions></code><p visible-if=\"wrong\">Certifique-se de escolher <code>?</code> seguido de <code>?</code> e depois <code>?</code>, <code>req.body.name</code>, <code>req.body.age</code>, <code>req.params.id</code>.</p></body></html>"
          },
